{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'gh pr review 7863 --request-changes --body $'\"'The diff is scoped correctly and the reported dynamic-access stats stay flat at 1/1, but this PR still fails the target native-image runtime verification. \"'`gh pr checks 7863` shows `com.github.luben:zstd-jni:1.5.7-10 [future-defaults-all] (GraalVM for JDK latest-ea @ ubuntu-latest)` failing, and the job log shows `native-image run` still throws `UnsatisfiedLinkError` for JNI symbols such as `ZstdCompressCtx.init()`, `ZstdOutputStreamNoFinalizer.recommendedCOutSize()`, `Zstd.defaultCompressionLevel()`, and `Zstd.compressBound()`.\n\nCompared with the currently supported `zstd-jni` metadata, the new metadata drops JNI-accessible coverage for types like `ZstdCompressCtx`/`ZstdDecompressCtx` and narrows the native library resource registration to `linux/amd64/libzstd-jni-1.5.7-10.so`, so the fix does not yet preserve native-image runtime behavior in the `future-defaults-all` lane. Please restore the missing JNI/resource metadata so that lane passes before approval.'\"'\"","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
