{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"agent_message","text":"Submitted a `CHANGES_REQUESTED` review directly on GitHub for PR `#7863`.\n\nBlocking issue: the PR is scoped correctly and the reported dynamic-access stats stay flat, but the target native-image runtime fix is still incomplete. `gh pr checks 7863` shows the `future-defaults-all` lane failing for `com.github.luben:zstd-jni:1.5.7-10`, and the Actions log shows `UnsatisfiedLinkError` for JNI symbols including `ZstdCompressCtx.init()`, `ZstdOutputStreamNoFinalizer.recommendedCOutSize()`, `Zstd.defaultCompressionLevel()`, and `Zstd.compressBound()`. I called out that the new metadata also drops JNI-accessible coverage present in the existing supported metadata and narrows native-library resource registration too aggressively.\n\nI did not run final index validation, because the PR was not in an approvable state."}}
